revision.text:
{{refimprove|date=September 2009}}

The '''Blinkenlights Archaeological Institute''' was established in 1997 to preserve historical [[computer|computing]] devices. Its headquarters are in [[Seattle]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]], United States. Some of its collection is on display at [[VintageTech]] in [[Oakland, California]], and the [[Computer History Museum]] in [[Mountain View, Santa Clara County, California|Mountain View, California]].

The name of the institute is a tribute to the term "[[blinkenlights]]" originated in [[Hacker (programmer subculture)|hacker]] humor.

