[[File:Bob Berman at IdeaFestival 2009.jpg|thumb|Bob Berman at IdeaFestival 2009]]
'''Robert Berman''', known as '''Bob Berman''', is an American [[astronomer]], author, and [[Popular science|science popularizer]].
He runs Overlook Observatory in [[Woodstock, New York]], USA. He was an [[adjunct professor]] of astronomy at the liberal arts college, [[Marymount Manhattan College]], from 1996 to 2000{{cn|date=March 2017}} and has appeared on ''[[CBS This Morning]]'', the ''[[Today (NBC program)|Today Show]]'', and the ''[[Late Show with David Letterman]]''.

==Biography==
In 1976, Berman founded the Catskill Astronomical Society.
From 1986 to 1994 he ran the summer astronomy program at [[Yellowstone National Park]]. He was the "Sky Lights" and "Night Watchman" astronomy columnist for ''[[Discover magazine|Discover]]'' from 1989 to 2006. He is currently ''[[Astronomy Magazine]]'''s "Strange Universe" columnist and contributing editor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astronomy.com/not-found|title=Houston, We've Had a Problem|publisher=}}</ref>

He also is the astronomy editor of ''[[The Old Farmer's Almanac]]''.<ref>http://www.digital-almanac.com/digitalalmanac/2009/?pg=84</ref> He has led [[Aurora (astronomy)|aurora]] and [[eclipse]] expeditions as far away as the [[Arctic]] and [[Antarctic]].

Berman conducts a weekly radio broadcast, "Skywindow", and a monthly, hour-long call-in show on [[Northeast Public Radio]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wamc.org/search.html?cx%3D008306176399346225959%3Aechwtlks1eq%26cof%3DFORID%3A11%26ie%3DUTF-8%26q%3Dbob+berman%26sa%3DSearch#1032 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-03-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728171154/http://www.wamc.org/search.html?cx=008306176399346225959%3Aechwtlks1eq&cof=FORID%3A11&ie=UTF-8&q=bob+berman&sa=Search#1032 |archivedate=2011-07-28 |df= }}</ref> He was keynote speaker at Starfest 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyaa.ca/index.php?page=sf.presentations|title=NYAA|first=North York Astronomical|last=Association|publisher=}}</ref>
He is also heard nightly on Slooh.com

