'''''Pirates: Captain's Quest''''' is a 1997 educational adventure video game. In Spain the game was published by Zeta Multimedia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tematika.com/pasatiempos/juegos_electronicos--3/computadoras--1/los_piratas_tu_gran_desafio--134588.htm|title=Los Piratas tu Gran Desafio - - Juegos|last=Tematika.com|website=www.tematika.com|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref>
== Plot == The game allows the player to take control of the pirate [[Blackbeard]] the 1700s, who on his quest to capture [[Christopher Columbus | Christopher Columbus']] ship [[Santa María (ship) | Santa Maria]] will allow the player to experience the pirating lifestyle with activities such as sword fighting, navigation, island conquering, and digging for buried treasure.
== Gameplay == Primarily an adventure game (due to requiring players to hunt for items and gather knowledge from characters to complete puzzles), the title contains 47 levels. It also contains minigames in other genres.
== Critical reception == Andy Backer of ''[[Computer Games Magazine]]'' positively compared it to Microprose's similarly-themed title [[Pirates! Gold|Pirates Gold]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cdmag.com/articles/001/144/pirates_captains_quest_review.html|title=Pirates: Captain’s Quest Review|date=2004-01-21|access-date=2017-02-03|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040121042724/http://www.cdmag.com/articles/001/144/pirates_captains_quest_review.html|archivedate=2004-01-21|df=}}</ref> J.P. Faber of U.S. Kids deemed it "terrifically fun" due to creating a historically authentic atmosphere.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Pirates:+captain's+quest.-a019585795|title=Pirates: captain's quest. - Free Online Library|website=www.thefreelibrary.com|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref> Daily Record thought thegame would keep kids entertained for hours, while educating them in the process.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/The+happy+shiny+club;+Shining+the+Holy+Ark:+Sega+Saturn-a061006862|title=The happy shiny club; Shining the Holy Ark: Sega Saturn. - Free Online Library|website=www.thefreelibrary.com|access-date=2017-02-03}}</ref>
